orestes.bloomfilter.redis

Class CBloomFilterRedis<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • orestes.bloomfilter.BloomFilter<T>
      • orestes.bloomfilter.CBloomFilter<T>
        • orestes.bloomfilter.redis.CBloomFilterRedis<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class CBloomFilterRedis<T>
extends CBloomFilter<T>
    Uses regular key-message pairs for counting instead of a bitarray. This introduces a space overhead but allows distribution of keys, thus increasing throughput. Pipelining can also be leveraged in this approach to minimize network latency.

      • makeTransient

        public void makeTransient(int ttl)
        Allows Redis to discard inserted objects after ttl seconds. However, there is no guarantee that the database actually removes these values. For deterministic removal remove(byte[]) should still be called.
        Parameters:
        ttl - the timespan in seconds after which Redis may discard an inserted element
